1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
Plates collide, pull apart, or slide — each creates unique hazards.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:08,000
These boundaries are alive with movement, shaping our planet.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,600
First, convergent boundaries: plates push together, causing intense earthquakes.

4
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:16,400
Next, divergent boundaries: where plates pull apart, magma rises, creating new land.

5
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:21,200
Finally, transform boundaries: plates slide past each other, often leading to tension.

6
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:25,200
Understanding these interactions helps us predict hazards and protect lives.

7
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,000
Curious to learn more about our planet?

8
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,600
Hit that follow button!
